relevance_user_prompt_template:
Return JSON with keys: relevant (bool), matched_topics (list[str]), topic_category (str), topic_method (str), rationale (str, <=40 words). Use both title and abstract and include slightly related precision-engineering papers.
Topics: {topics_json}
Topic taxonomy: {topic_taxonomy_json}
Title: {title}
Abstract: {abstract}

batch_relevance_user_prompt_template:
Return a JSON object with key "decisions" (list). Each decision item MUST include: id (str), relevant (bool), matched_topics (list[str]), topic_category (str), topic_method (str), rationale (str <= 30 words). Evaluate using both title and abstract.
Topics: {topics_json}
Topic taxonomy: {topic_taxonomy_json}
Papers: {papers_json}
Include one decision for every input paper id.

analysis_user_prompt_template:
Write a concise markdown report using short sections and tables. Avoid long paragraphs and generic background.
Must include:
1) Collaboration by category table using the taxonomy in input.
2) Partner focus table: partner name, type (University/Company/Other), dominant category, paper count.
3) Most important research advancements/breakthroughs (bullet list, brief, evidence-based).
4) Future direction analysis from observed collaborations.
5) Interesting trend highlights.

Input topics: {topics_json}
Relevant paper count: {relevant_count}
Tagged stats: {stats_json}
Tagged paper sample: {paper_sample_json}

report_user_prompt_template:
Write a concise report with markdown tables and short bullets.
Must include: 
1) Category relevance table (which papers align to which category of interest).
2) University-to-company research focus table (partner, type, dominant category, paper count).
3) Most important breakthroughs (short bullets, evidence-based).
4) Future directions given current collaborations (short bullets).
5) Interesting trends from year/category or method/category data.
Avoid too much text; get straight to the point.

Input topics: {topics_json}
Relevant paper count: {relevant_count}
Tagged stats: {stats_json}
Tagged paper sample: {paper_sample_json}
